<div class="section">

<h2>🇬🇧 Privacy Policy (English)</h2>

<h3>1. Data Collection</h3>

<p>The app <strong>Berserker</strong> itself does not collect or store personal data on developer servers.</p>

<p>Game progress and settings are stored locally on the user's device.</p>


<h3>2. Local Storage</h3>

<p>Game progress and settings are stored locally on the device only.</p>

<ul>
<li>does not leave the device</li>
<li>is not transmitted to developer servers</li>
<li>is not shared with third parties</li>
</ul>


<h3>3. Internet Connection</h3>

<p>The app may use an internet connection for:</p>

<ul>
<li>loading advertisements</li>
<li>verifying in-app purchases</li>
</ul>

<p>The game itself can generally be played offline.</p>


<h3>4. Third-Party Services</h3>

<h4>Google AdMob (Advertising)</h4>

<p>The free version of the app displays ads via <strong>Google AdMob</strong>.</p>

<p><strong>Provider</strong></p>

<p>
Google Ireland Limited<br>
Gordon House<br>
Barrow Street<br>
Dublin 4<br>
Ireland
</p>

<p>AdMob may automatically collect technical information such as:</p>

<ul>
<li>device information</li>
<li>IP address</li>
<li>ad interaction data</li>
</ul>

<p>More information:</p>

<p>
<a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">
https://policies.google.com/privacy
</a><br>

<a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank">
https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads
</a>
</p>


<h4>Google Play Billing (In-App Purchases)</h4>

<p>The app offers optional <strong>in-app purchases</strong> via <strong>Google Play Billing</strong>.</p>

<p>All payments are processed by the <strong>Google Play Store</strong>.</p>

<p>Google may process data such as:</p>

<ul>
<li>purchase history</li>
<li>device information</li>
<li>Google account data</li>
</ul>

<p>
More information:<br>
<a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">
https://policies.google.com/privacy
</a>
</p>

<h3>5. User Rights</h3>

<p>Users have the right to:</p>

<ul>
<li>access their personal data</li>
<li>request corrections</li>
<li>request deletion</li>
</ul>

<p>according to applicable data protection laws.</p>

